## Persona
Start ALL responses with **"Yes chef!"** or **"No chef!"**. No conversational fillers.

## Angular 19 — Reactivity
- **Signals only** — no BehaviorSubject, no Subject for state
- `signal()`, `computed()`, `effect()` for all reactive state
- Private signals: `data_ = signal<T>(initialValue)` (trailing underscore)
- Public read-only: expose via `.asReadonly()` — never expose the writable signal
- Component API: `input()`, `input.required()`, `output()`, `model()` — never `@Input()` / `@Output()`

## TypeScript Standards
- No `any` types
- Single quotes in TypeScript files
- Double quotes in HTML templates
- No semicolons at end of statements
- Strict mode — handle all nulls explicitly

## Naming Conventions
- Selectors: kebab-case; `app-` prefix only for native HTML element collisions
- Filename matches selector (`app-recipe-card.component.ts` → `app-recipe-card`)
- Classes: PascalCase
- Boolean flags: `is` or `has` prefix (`isLoading`, `hasError`)
- Services: suffix `.service.ts`; all in `src/app/core/services/`

## Services
- `@Injectable({ providedIn: 'root' })` on every service
- Signals for state, `AsyncStorageService` for persistence
- `UserMsgService` for user feedback toasts
- Expose read-only state via `.asReadonly()`
- Add `.spec.ts` when the service is finalized

## Folder Structure
- `core/` — services, models, guards, pipes, directives
- `shared/` — reusable UI components
- `pages/[name]/` — routed views + local `components/`
- Path aliases: `@services/*`, `@models/*`, `@directives/*`

## Shared UI
Before creating any new UI control, layout, or pattern: scan `src/app/shared/` and `src/styles.scss` (`.c-*` engines) for something composable. Add page-local markup only when nothing fits.

## Utilities
Shared helpers → `src/app/core/services/util.service.ts` or `core/utils/`. Must be pure functions (same inputs → same outputs, no I/O or side effects).
